						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">FrankenGraphics wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">-Gif runs at 60fps. You browser may or may not display it correctly. <br /></div>Very unimportant, and giving in to pedantry: 50Hz, not 60. But that's just as well, because GIF animations only support frame intervals that are multiples of 10ms, so you can't get an even 60Hz anyway.<br /><br />But actually about the gameplay merits...<br /><br />For some reason my brain is having a hard time parsing some of the walls... basically I'm parsing the shadows correctly, but the thin edges (such as the ochre floor in the lower left corner of the lower screen, which is higher than the teal walkway center-left) just don't feel obvious to me.</div>

